As of September 3, 2020, the Ukrainian government announced that from September 7 new epidemic zoning will start to operate. This means that in those red zones educational institutions, including preschool facilities and schools, should be closed. 
Red zones include:
The cities of Ivano-Frankivsk, Kolomyia, Kalush, Kosiv, and Tysmenytsia districts of the Ivano-Frankivsk region;
The towns of Bilyaivka and Izmail, and the Bolhradskyi district of the Odesa region;
The town of Dubno, and Kostopil district of Rivne region;
The cities of Ternopil, Berezhany and Chortkiv, Berezhany, Buchach, Husiatyn, Monastyrsky, Terebovliansky, Ternopilsky, and Chortkivsky districts of the Ternopil region;
Velykyi Burluk district of Kharkiv region;
The city of Chernivtsi, Vyzhnytsia, Hlyboka, Zastava, Kitzman, Novoselytsia, and Storozhynets districts of the Chernivtsi region; and
Bobrovytskyi district of Chernihiv region.

