December 10, 2020, Ukraine. The Ministry of Health has developed a new sanitary regulation for institutions of general secondary education. Students living at a distance of more than 2 km from the educational institution are provided with transport for transportation to school;
All school employees must undergo mandatory preventive examinations. In case of violation of the terms of preventive examinations, employees are not allowed to work;
Students who often suffer from colds, rheumatism, tonsillitis are recommended to be placed in the third row, that is, against the inner wall;
Educational institutions should have internal sanitary facilities, because every tenth school in Ukraine has an external toilet, which carries the risk of urological and genitourinary diseases in children.

February 17, 2020, Ukraine. From February 24, adaptive quarantine will be introduced in Ukraine. 
Red zones: Educational institutions will not work (except for kindergartens and primary classes in schools);

Update: As of March 16, 2021, it was announced by the Government of Ukraine that the quarantine measures in educational institutions are still present and students of 5-11 grades of general secondary education, students of vocational education, and students of vocational higher and higher education should continue being on a distance learning. UPDATE: Update: As of March 16, 2021, it was announced by the Government of Ukraine that the quarantine measures in educational institutions are still present and students of 5-11 grades of general secondary education, students of vocational education, and students of vocational higher and higher education should continue being on a distance learning.

